## Difference Between Sequential and Conditional Workflows

| Sequential Workflow | Conditional Workflow |
|----------------------|----------------------|
| Executes every node | Executes only selected nodes |
| Fixed execution path | Dynamic execution path |
| No decision making | Decision-based routing |
| Simpler | More flexible |
| Best for linear tasks | Best for intelligent applications |

